item.dc:creator: @the_wanderer The Wanderer
item.description:
@the_wanderer wrote:

Have you tried putting javac instead of “C:\blah blah blah”? If your environment variables are set correctly, you shouldn’t need to put that there. And no, it is not Java\jre6. It is Java\jdk. If you don’t have jdk then you have not installed it. JRE is for running Java applications, JDK is for compiling them.

item.dc:creator: @Team_Rocket Team_Rocket
item.description:
@Team_Rocket wrote:

Try one of these:

  1. Take out the Classpath, if it isn’t the problem put it back in.
  2. Make sure the whole path is correct, not just your Java.
  3. Re-check your variables.
  4. Uninstall your Java and update to the latest version.
